<item>
            <title>[HBASE-1184] HColumnDescriptor is a little too restrictive with family names</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1184</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;HColumnDescriptor crrently requires of its family names that they be letters, digits, underscores or periods.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Character.isLetterOrDigit(b&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;i&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;) || b&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;i&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; == &apos;_&apos; || b&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;i&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; == &apos;.&apos;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It would be nice if it let rather more characters be used (personally, I&apos;d like to use a hyphen!)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
